    "body": "### Problem\n\nUpdating to the newest treesitter (0.12.1) and opening a file causes this error:\n\n```\nError in BufReadPost Autocommands for \"*\":\nLua callback: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/filetype.lua:28: BufReadPost Autocommands for \"*\"..FileType Autocommands for \"*\"..function <SNR>1_LoadFTPlugin[20]..script /usr/share/nvim/runtime/ftplugin/lua.lua: Vim(runtime):E5113: Lu\na chunk: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/highlighter.lua:279: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/query.lua:374: Query error at 74:3. Invalid field name \"operator\":\n  operator: _ @operator)\n  ^\n\nstack traceback:\n        [C]: in function 'error'\n        /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/highlighter.lua:279: in function 'get_query'\n        /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/highlighter.lua:109: in function 'set_conceal_lines'\n        /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/highlighter.lua:157: in function 'new'\n        /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter.lua:450: in function 'start'\n        /usr/share/nvim/runtime/ftplugin/lua.lua:2: in main chunk\n        [C]: in function 'nvim_cmd'\n        /usr/share/nvim/runtime/filetype.lua:28: in function </usr/share/nvim/runtime/filetype.lua:27>\n        [C]: in function 'pcall'\n        vim/_core/shared.lua: in function <vim/_core/shared.lua:0>\n        [C]: in function '_with'\n        /usr/share/nvim/runtime/filetype.lua:27: in function </usr/share/nvim/runtime/filetype.lua:10>\nstack traceback:\n        [C]: in function '_with'\n        /usr/share/nvim/runtime/filetype.lua:27: in function </usr/share/nvim/runtime/filetype.lua:10>\n```\n\nThis only seems to occur with the lua parser?  None of the other parsers (c, markdown, etc) seem to have caused this error.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```sh\nnvim foo.lua\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nEnter `foo.lua` without error.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.1 commit aa9271466e7e\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nunsure, this is related to tree-sitter\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nChimera Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nfoot 1.26.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nfoot\n\n### Installation\n\nChimera Linux Package Index; apk",
